The colour pattern of the carapace of
M. angustus
was described as white or pinkish yellow, marbled with orange-brown, with a narrow median stripe extending from the posterior margin of to the point in front of the lateral spine ( Rathbun 1900 ; Werding 1977 ). This description corresponds well to the illustrations of the colour pattern of
M. angustus
from Panama ( Fig. 17 ) and Honduras in Gore & Shoup (1968) , as well as to the colour photos of the Brazilian specimens (
Almeida et al. 2010
; Mantelatto & Miranda 2016 ;
Mantelatto et al. 2021
).
